incus-ui is a browser frontend for Incus.

It enables easy and accessible container and virtual machine
management. It targets small and large scale private clouds.

Building for 32bit is currently not supported.

This SlackBuild uses a maintainer generated source tarball since
upstream does not publish release tarballs. Anyone wishing to generate
their own source tarball may do so by running the included
get-incus-ui.sh bash script.

In order to avoid network access while building, this SlackBuild also
uses a maintainer generated tarball of node modules needed by nodejs
to build the browser. It may be locally regenerated by removing the
existing *-NM.tar.lz file and running the incus-ui.SlackBuild script
which will download the required node modules and bundle them into a
tarball; then run incus-ui.SlackBuild to build the package.
